- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper introduces a new method for change-point detection in evolving networks, which could have implications for software engineering. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a probabilistic learning framework and Bayesian hypothesis testing to solve the change-point detection problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing dynamic systems (evolving networks) and detecting changes in their behavior. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper introduces a new algorithmic method for change-point detection in evolving networks.
